article.description: — Trenton McLaughlin sank a go-ahead 3-pointer with three seconds left, scoring 20 points to rally Northern Arizona to a 76-75 victory over Incarnate Word on Saturday night.
article.headline: McLaughlin scores 20 as Northern Arizona beats Incarnate Word 76-75
article.linkText: McLaughlin scores 20 as Northern Arizona beats Incarnate Word 76-75
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Trenton McLaughlin sank a go-ahead 3-pointer with three seconds left, scoring 20 points to rally Northern Arizona to a 76-75 victory over Incarnate Word on Saturday night. McLaughlin was 8 of 18 shooting (4 for 8 from 3-point range) for the Lumberjacks (5-5). Diego Campisano scored 17 points and added seven rebounds. Jayden Jackson shot 4 of 8 from the field and 6 for 7 from the line to finish with 14 points. The Cardinals (3-6) were led by Sky Wicks, who recorded 28 points. Shon Robinson added 27 points and eight rebounds for Incarnate Word. In addition, Dylan Hayman finished with five points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
